Cerro Conejo Member, Zia Formation (late Barstovian; 
Tedford and Barghoorn, 1997
), Sandoval County, northern Albuquerque Basin, 
New Mexico
: F:AM 62144, partial skeleton with crushed skull with I1–C, alveolus of P2, P3–M1, partial left ramus with c, alveolus of p2, p3–m1, left and right humerus, radius, ulna, femur and tibia, partial scapulae, vertebrae, articulated pelvis, left and right calcaneus, assorted left and right metatarsal bones, and assorted phalanges, Rincon Quarry.
